# Canvas API knowledge

Before writing or changing any code that calls the Canvas API, read
`docs/canvas-api-knowledge.md` — a curated summary of the official Instructure
developer docs (https://developerdocs.instructure.com). Key facts:

- This project uses the **GraphQL** API: single endpoint `POST {CANVAS_BASE_URL}/graphql`,
  body `{query, variables, operationName?}`. `CANVAS_BASE_URL` must end at `/api`
  (never `/api/v1` — that is the REST base).
- GraphQL `id` is a base64 Relay global id; `_id` is the traditional numeric REST id.
  `course(id:)`, `node(id:)`, and `legacyNode(type:, _id:)` are the lookup fields;
  `course(id:)` accepts either id form.
- Collections paginate via Relay connections: `somethingConnection(first:, after:)`
  with `pageInfo { endCursor hasNextPage }`. Keep page sizes reasonable.
- The GraphQL schema is incomplete vs REST; explore it in GraphiQL at
  `https://<institution>.instructure.com/graphiql`, and fall back to REST
  (`/api/v1/...`, Link-header pagination) when a field is missing.
- Auth is `Authorization: Bearer <token>`. Manual profile tokens are for personal
  testing only; multi-user distribution requires OAuth2 (1-hour tokens + refresh).
- Handle `429` (rate limited — retry later) and `401` with `WWW-Authenticate`
  header (bad/expired token or wrong Canvas domain).
- To look up any other Canvas resource, append `.md` to a developerdocs URL or ask
  the docs directly: `GET https://developerdocs.instructure.com/get_started.md?ask=<question>`.
